    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>
                <add>ב"ה באלטימארע יום א' ט"ו סיון תריול כ"ג</add>
            </p>
            <p>
                <placeName>No 87 N. Howard <sic>st.</sic></placeName>
            </p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>Mon., June 8 1857</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Baltimore</placeName>, <date>Sunday, 15<hi rend="sup"
                        >th</hi> of Sivan (June) 1857</date></p>
            <p>To my friend:</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><date>Friday</date> evening, just before the <date>Sabbath</date> an
                English<lb/> prayer book of the Sephardic ritual was ordered from me. It
                    <add>?</add><lb/> be in the best binding, gilt, bound as prettily as is
                possible<lb/> It may cost as much as $6, but it must be here
                <date>Wednesday</date><lb/> evening, or at the latest <date>Thursday</date>. If you,
                my friend,<lb/> have such a one, or can have it prepared so that I<lb/> can have it
                by <date>Wednesday</date> or <date>Thursday</date> by Adams<lb/> Express, you can
                send it to me and I shall sell it<lb/> for you. But it must be bound most elegantly,
                other<lb/>wise all the trouble is in vain. This is what the man<lb/> demanded. I am
                not acquainted with him.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">With the blessing of peace.</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <persName role="author">Abraham Rice</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <placeName>#87 No. Howard St.</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
